Rev, only $800 on predictit, that might have been the limit back then but not sure. I spread it over five other sites/betting parlors/books.

As I tweeted a few months ago I made a large bet against Senator Bernie Sanders becoming the Democratic Pres. nominee. I thought it was $ in the bank even though I was getting back only about +$170 for every $800 I bet. Suffice to say, up to a week ago (or less) Sanders was the

big favorite to get the nomination and I was getting killed on the gamble. I just closed out the trade for a ridiculously small +$18 profit per each $800 I bet. All I can say, "phew." I got out alive. And I will never ever bet on politics again (that was my first bet ever)!

Yes and there is a gravitational pull of stocks higher (+7% year for as long as the eyes could see back). So you got that not working for you on the short side. As well, reward v risk is asymmetrical on shorts, you can lose an infinite amount but can make only 100%.
